citation: Proclamation under the Human Cloning and Other Prohibited Practices Act 2003 (Tas)
text:
Proclamation under the Human Cloning and Other Prohibited Practices Act 2003

I, the Governor in and over the State of Tasmania and its Dependencies in the Commonwealth of Australia, acting with the advice of the Executive Council, by this my proclamation made under section 2 of the Human Cloning and Other Prohibited Practices Act 2003 fix 1 December 2003 as the day on which the provisions of that Act commence.

17 November 2003

RICHARD BUTLER

Governor

By His Excellency's Command,

D. E. LLEWELLYN

Minister for Health and Human Services

Displayed and numbered in accordance with the Rules Publication Act 1953.

Notified in the Gazette on 26 November 2003

This proclamation is administered in the Department of Health and Human Services.
